Thanks. I will correct it.

- Download the `mobilenet 368x368` weights/checkpoint files (as linked in the readme)
- Adapt the paths in `networks.py` so that the downloaded files get restored (`loader.restore` should be called with something like `'[PATH_TO_DOWNLOADED_CHECKPOINT_FOLDER]/model-388003'` without any file extensions)
yes ,you should change to 1.3.

1. I split input batch and everything here : https://github.com/ildoonet/tf-openpose/blob/master/train.py#L73

2. do forward pass with splitted batch on each gpus. : https://github.com/ildoonet/tf-openpose/blob/master/train.py#L82

3. When I compute the loss, all the informations are gathered : https://github.com/ildoonet/tf-openpose/blob/master/train.py#L110

4. Also, When gradients are computed, each gradients will be assigned to gpus which calculate the gradient and update the shared weights. : https://github.com/ildoonet/tf-openpose/blob/master/train.py#L129

There are few things I have to implement more. I will update this repo as soon as I have a time..

Also this questions is duplicated : https://github.com/ildoonet/tf-openpose/issues/3
i will. I have to change and implement more. After this, I will clean codes and add more explanations.
